title: For Sale:  1941 VKT M39
postcontent: 1941 VKT M39 Finnish Capture Mosin Nagant RifleThis one has some very desirable features including:-Original Wartime Stock with correct finger joints-“SA” marking indicating that is was a Finnish Army Rifle-D marked barrel indicating that it was accurized by the Finns when reworked-Very nice “Tiger Striping” wood grain, which is saught after in these rifles-Remnants of original Russian markings on receiver where the Finns machined their removalFor those unfamiliar....At then end of 1939 as WW2 was ramping up, the Rusians tried to occupy Finland.  They were unsuccesful for debatable reasons, but a popular explanation was that the Finns were incredible engineers and even better marksmen.  As they killed Russians, they captured their Mosin Nagant rifles.  They reworked the rifles rebarreling them, upgrading triggers, shortening overall length and accurizing them tremendously.  Essentially the Finns used Russian rifles to kill Russians.  This rifle is an extremely beautiful example of this saga.$500 through FFL transfer....This rifle is eligible for C&R licensee
